        "Text": {
          "type": "cexolocstring",
          "value": {
            "0": "You can raise your magic skill levels by casting spells during combat. For example, to raise your Evocation skill you can cast \"Fire Blast\" on an enemy during combat. When the enemy dies, you'll receive skill XP towards the Evocation skill.\n\nIt's important to note that, in general, XP is only gained during combat. This is an intentional design decision to prevent \"skill spamming\". For this reason, beneficial spells like \"Recover\" will only give XP if you use them during combat."
          }
        }
