        "Text": {
          "type": "cexolocstring",
          "value": {
            "0": "Mana naturally regenerates over time. This occurs without you needing to do anything. However, it is very slow and you'll want to find other ways to replenish it.\n\nThere are a number of ways to quickly recover mana but the most common one is by purchasing the \"Meditate\" perk. This will enable you to quickly recover mana so long as you stay in place and don't enter combat. This perk can be found in the \"General\" category of the perk menu.\n\nIn addition to that, there are a number of items like potions and kits which can be used to restore mana. You can also increase your natural mana regeneration by equipping armor with a bonus to this stat.\n\nFinally, mana regeneration can be increased by improving your charisma stat. You'll receive +1 to natural mana regeneration for every two charisma past 10."
          }
        }
